requestinterwiki-button-copy: Text for the 'Copy to Clipboard' button.
requestinterwiki-comment-given: Displayed if a custom comment is given. $1 is the handler's username.
requestinterwiki-comment-success: Message displayed when a comment is successfully added to the request.
requestinterwiki-duplicate-request: Message displayed when user attempts to submit a request that is to similar to an existing open request.
requestinterwiki-edit-success: Message displayed when the request is successfully edited.
requestinterwiki-info-command: The generated command that is displayed on the 'handling' section of Special:RequestInterwikiQueue. $1 is the generated command.
requestinterwiki-info-filesize: The file size for the uploaded XML file. $1 is the file size.
requestinterwiki-info-groups: User groups that the requester has on the target wiki. Displayed on the 'handling' section of Special:RequestInterwikiQueue. $1 is the requester's username; $2 is the target wiki's database name; $3 is the comma separated list of user groups.
requestinterwiki-info-interwiki: The information displayed on the 'handling' section of Special:RequestInterwikiQueue, when there is no interwiki prefix present, and you have the necessary rights to insert a prefix. $1 is the target database name.
requestinterwiki-info-no-file-found: Message displayed instead of generated command and file size, if the file for the request is not found. $1 is the full path to the file.
requestinterwiki-info-no-interwiki-prefi: Message that is displayed on the 'handling' section of Special:RequestInterwikiQueue when no interwiki prefix is found on the target wiki, which is pointing to the source wiki. $1 is the target wiki; $2 is the source wiki's hostname.
requestinterwiki-info-request-private: Message that is displayed on the 'handling' section of Special:RequestInterwikiQueue when viewing a request that is private.
requestinterwiki-info-requester-globally: Message that is displayed on the 'handling' section of Special:RequestInterwikiQueue when the requester has been globally blocked. $1 is the requester's username.
requestinterwiki-info-requester-locally-: Message that is displayed on the 'handling' section of Special:RequestInterwikiQueue when the requester has been locally blocked on the current wiki. $1 is the requester's username; $2 is the current wiki's ID.
requestinterwiki-info-requester-locked: Message that is displayed on the 'handling' section of Special:RequestInterwikiQueue when the requester has been locked. $1 is the requester's username.
requestinterwiki-interwiki-failed: Error message displayed when submitting the interwiki table changes fails. $1 is the target database name.
requestinterwiki-interwiki-success: Success message displayed when submitting the interwiki table changes successfully. $1 is the target database name.
requestinterwiki-invalid-interwiki-url: Status message displayed when invalid URL was entered for the 'url' field for adding interwiki.
requestinterwiki-invalid-target: Status message displayed when invalid database name was entered for the 'target' field.
requestinterwiki-label-add-comment: Label for the 'Add Comment' submit button.
requestinterwiki-label-edit-request: Label for the 'Edit Request' submit button.
requestinterwiki-label-interwiki-prefix: Label for the interwiki prefix field.
requestinterwiki-label-interwiki-url: Label for the interwiki URL field. $1 is an example URL that can be entered here. It is displayed as <scheme>://<host>/wiki/$1. The scheme and host are populated by parsing the source URL for the request.
requestinterwiki-label-status-updated-co: Label for the optional comment field in the 'handling' section of Special:RequestInterwikiQueue.
requestinterwiki-label-update-status: Label for the update status select field in the 'handling' section of Special:RequestInterwikiQueue.
requestinterwiki-no-changes: Message displayed if attempting to edit request without making any changes.
requestinterwiki-notcentral:
Heading for the message displayed if there is a configured central wiki, and it is not the current wiki.
{{Identical|Disabled}}
requestinterwiki-notcentral-text: Text for the message displayed if there is a configured central wiki, and it is not the current wiki.
requestinterwiki-notification-body-new-r: Echo notification body for 'requestinterwiki-new-request'. $1 is reason; $2 is the requester's username; $3 is the target wiki's database name.
requestinterwiki-notification-header-com: Echo notification header for 'requestinterwiki-request-comment'. $1 is the request ID.
requestinterwiki-notification-header-new: Echo notification header for 'requestinterwiki-new-request'. $1 is the request ID.
requestinterwiki-notification-header-sta: Echo notification header for 'requestinterwiki-request-status-update'. $1 is the request ID.
requestinterwiki-notloggedin: Error message if user tries to request an import dump while not being logged in.
requestinterwiki-private: Error message if a user tries to view an import dump request that is marked as private and they do not have access to it.
requestinterwiki-request-edited: 'Request edited' message. $1 is the actor's username; $2 is the changes that were made.
requestinterwiki-request-edited-reason: Message displayed if the value of 'reason' was edited. $1 is the previous value; $2 is the new value.
requestinterwiki-request-edited-source: Message displayed if the value of 'source' was edited. $1 is the previous value; $2 is the new value.
requestinterwiki-request-edited-target: Message displayed if the value of 'target' was edited. $1 is the previous value; $2 is the new value.
requestinterwiki-request-locked: Message displayed above the form at Special:RequestInterwikiQueue if the request is locked.
requestinterwiki-request-reopened: 'Request reopened' message. $1 is the actor's username; $2 is the changes that were made.
requestinterwiki-section-comments:
'Request Comments' section label.
{{doc-important|This means "comments about the request", not "ask for comments"}}
requestinterwiki-section-details:
'Request Details' section label.
{{doc-important|This means "details about the request", not "ask for details"}}
requestinterwiki-status-updated: Fixed comment given to requester when the status is updated. $1 is status.
requestinterwiki-status-updated-success: Message displayed when the status of the request is successfully updated.
requestinterwiki-success: Message after an import dump request has been successfully submitted.
requestinterwiki-success-locked: Message displayed when a request has been successfully locked.
requestinterwiki-success-private: Message displayed when a request has been successfully marked as private.
requestinterwiki-success-public: Message displayed when a request has been successfully marked as public.
requestinterwiki-success-unlocked: Message displayed when a request has been successfully unlocked.
requestinterwiki-table-requested-date: 'Requested Date' label for the table on Special:RequestInterwikiQueue.
requestinterwiki-table-requester: 'Requester' label for the table on Special:RequestInterwikiQueue.
requestinterwiki-table-status: 'Status' label for the table on Special:RequestInterwikiQueue.
requestinterwiki-table-target: 'Target' label for the table on Special:RequestInterwikiQueue.
requestinterwiki-unknown: Message displayed if the request is not found.
requestinterwiki-usergroups-none: Displayed value if the requester has no user groups on the target wiki.
requestinterwikiprivate-log-header: Header for the RequestInterwiki private log.
ipb-action-request-import-dump: The label for the action select option on [[Special:Block]] to block a user from requesting import dumps.
